        ],
        [
          "Classification",
          "Intelligent Tutoring System",
          "Next Question is Correct",
          "Correct (1) vs Incorrect (0)",
          "1709 ASSISTments17 learners, 3852 ASSISTments09 learners\n\n",
          "ASSISTments",
          "Sequence of Answers, Question Test",
          "[Sequence of Answers, Questions and Concepts]",
          "Attention-based KT models are the curent state-of-the-art on multiple datasets. However, most of them assume that the pool of questions does not change after the training of the model. \n\nAdding questions in online settings would lead to an increase of the input dimension.\n\nMoreover, the changes in behavior of the learners introduce distributional drift. \n",
          "The proposed model uses an attention mechanism for questions and concepts that increases dynamically while preserving the information provided by the pre-existing pool of questions. \n\nIn addition, the model weights are regularized.",
          "This model is based on AKT with a change in the question-concept mapping. \n\nThis approach involves the ability to increase the dimensionality of the attention module whether it is because of the introduction of new concepts or the introduction of new questions.\n\nThis is done by copying the weights of the previous question while initializing the new weights for the new question using Rasch embedding.",
          "J-AKT, D-AKT, ARAIKT, ARAIKT without reg",
          "5-Fold Cross-Validation",
          "AST17- 04/05\n{AUC: 0.7331 - ARAIKT, Accuracy: 0.6972 - ARAIKT}\n\nAST09\n{AUC: 0.6750 - ARAIKT, Accuracy: 0.6838 - ARAIKT}\n\n",
          "Authors propose a change to the attention representation of AKT and show that it outperforms AKT on the tested dataset. \n\nAuthors also perform an ablation study to showcase the improtance of having regularization or not.",
          "Needs valdiation on additional datasets. "
        ]
      ],
      "index": 9
    }
